<A HREF='B19C049.htm'>Psalms 49</A></P><CENTER><H2 ALIGN=CENTER>The Book of     
Psalms</H2></CENTER><P><A HREF='index.htm'>Return to Index</A>.</P><CENTER>     
<TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=5 WIDTH=90%><TR><TD></TD><TD><CENTER><H1>Chapter    
50</H1></CENTER></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V1><H4>1</H4></TD><TD><P>  
The mighty ELOHIYM, even YHVH, hath spoken, and called the earth from the       
rising of the sun unto the going down thereof.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP> 
<A NAME=V2><H4>2</H4></TD><TD><P>Out of Zion, the perfection of beauty, ELOHIYM 
hath shined.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V3><H4>3</H4></TD><TD><P>  
Our ELOHIYM shall come, and shall not keep silence: a fire shall devour before  
him, and it shall be very tempestuous round about him.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD     
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V4><H4>4</H4></TD><TD><P>He shall call to the heavens from   
above, and to the earth, that he may judge his people.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD     
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V5><H4>5</H4></TD><TD><P>Gather my saints together unto me;  
those that have made a covenant with me by sacrifice.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD      
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V6><H4>6</H4></TD><TD><P>And the heavens shall declare his   
righteousness: for ELOHIYM is judge himself. Selah.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD        
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V7><H4>7</H4></TD><TD><P>Hear, O my people, and I will       
speak; O Israel, and I will testify against thee: I am ELOHIYM, even thy        
ELOHIYM.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V8><H4>8</H4></TD><TD><P>I     
will not reprove thee for thy sacrifices or thy burnt offerings, to have been   
continually before me.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V9><H4>9</H4>    
</TD><TD><P>I will take no bullock out of thy house, nor he goats out of thy    
folds.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V10><H4>10</H4></TD><TD><P>For   
every beast of the forest is mine, and the cattle upon a thousand hills.</P>    
</TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V11><H4>11</H4></TD><TD><P>I know all the  
fowls of the mountains: and the wild beasts of the field are mine.</P></TD></TR>
<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V12><H4>12</H4></TD><TD><P>If I were hungry, I would 
not tell thee: for the world is mine, and the fulness thereof.</P></TD></TR><TR>
<TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V13><H4>13</H4></TD><TD><P>Will I eat the flesh of       
bulls, or drink the blood of goats?</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V14>
<H4>14</H4></TD><TD><P>Offer unto ELOHIYM thanksgiving; and pay thy vows unto   
the ELYOWN:</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V15><H4>15</H4></TD><TD><P> 
And call upon me in the day of trouble: I will deliver thee, and thou shalt     
glorify me.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V16><H4>16</H4></TD><TD><P> 
But unto the wicked ELOHIYM saith, What hast thou to do to declare my statutes, 
or that thou shouldest take my covenant in thy mouth?</P></TD></TR><TR><TD      
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V17><H4>17</H4></TD><TD><P>Seeing thou hatest instruction,   
and casteth my words behind thee.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V18>  
<H4>18</H4></TD><TD><P>When thou sawest a thief, then thou consentedst with     
him, and hast been partaker with adulterers.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A 
NAME=V19><H4>19</H4></TD><TD><P>Thou givest thy mouth to evil, and thy tongue   
frameth deceit.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V20><H4>20</H4></TD><TD>
<P>Thou sittest and speakest against thy brother; thou slanderest thine own     
mother's son.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V21><H4>21</H4></TD><TD>  
<P>These things hast thou done, and I kept silence; thou thoughtest that I was  
altogether such an one as thyself: but I will reprove thee, and set them in     
order before thine eyes.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V22><H4>22</H4>
</TD><TD><P>Now consider this, ye that forget ELOAHH, lest I tear you in        
pieces, and there be none to deliver.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A        
NAME=V23><H4>23</H4></TD><TD><P>Whoso offereth praise glorifieth me: and to him 
that ordereth his conversation aright will I shew the salvation of ELOHIYM.</P> 
</TD></TR></TABLE><!--This Software is copyright 2000 by John M. Hurt, PO Box   
